<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta content='text/html; charset=UTF-8' http-equiv='Content-Type' />
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: #333;
      }
      .container {
        max-width: 600px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 20px;
      }
      .header {
        background-color: #ef4444;
        color: white;
        padding: 20px;
        text-align: center;
        border-radius: 8px 8px 0 0;
      }
      .content {
        background-color: #fef2f2;
        padding: 20px;
        border: 1px solid #fecaca;
        border-top: none;
        border-radius: 0 0 8px 8px;
      }
      .footer {
        text-align: center;
        padding: 20px;
        color: #6b7280;
        font-size: 14px;
      }
      .button {
        display: inline-block;
        padding: 10px 20px;
        background-color: #3b82f6;
        color: white;
        text-decoration: none;
        border-radius: 5px;
        margin-top: 15px;
      }
      .error-box {
        background-color: white;
        padding: 15px;
        border-radius: 5px;
        margin: 15px 0;
        border: 1px solid #fca5a5;
      }
      .label {
        font-weight: bold;
        color: #991b1b;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="header">
        <h1>Report Generation Failed</h1>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 18px;"><%= @scheduled_report.name %></p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="content">
        <p>Hello,</p>
        
        <p>We were unable to generate your scheduled report "<strong><%= @scheduled_report.name %></strong>". The report generation process encountered an error.</p>
        
        <div class="error-box">
          <p><span class="label">Report Query:</span><br>
          <%= @scheduled_report.query %></p>
          
          <p><span class="label">Attempted:</span><br>
          <%= Time.current.strftime("%B %d, %Y at %l:%M %p %Z") %></p>
          
          <% if @error_message.present? %>
            <p><span class="label">Error Details:</span><br>
            <%= @error_message %></p>
          <% end %>
        </div>
        
        <p><strong>What you can do:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Check if your query is correctly formatted</li>
          <li>Ensure the dataset is still accessible and contains data</li>
          <li>Verify that any referenced columns or fields still exist</li>
          <li>Try running the query manually to identify any issues</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>You can review and edit your scheduled report settings in your dashboard:</p>
        
        <%= link_to "View Scheduled Report", scheduled_report_url(@scheduled_report), class: "button", style: "color: white;" %>
        
        <div class="error-box" style="margin-top: 20px;">
          <p style="margin: 0;"><span class="label">Next Attempt:</span><br>
          <% if @scheduled_report.next_run_at && @scheduled_report.enabled? %>
            We will attempt to generate this report again on <%= @scheduled_report.next_run_at.strftime("%B %d, %Y at %l:%M %p %Z") %>
          <% else %>
            This report is currently disabled or not scheduled for future runs.
          <% end %>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="footer">
        <p>This is an automated error notification from QuantumQuery.</p>
        <p>If you continue to experience issues, please contact our support team.</p>
        <p>&copy; <%= Date.current.year %> QuantumQuery. All rights reserved.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>